Jenni Evans, News24Johannesburg &ndash; A construction worker was critically injured after falling down three storeys at a construction site in Fourways, paramedics said on Saturday.The 23-year-old man had to be rescued from the foundations of the site with the use of ropes, a construction bucket and a crane, said ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak.They were called out just before midnight on Friday and the rescue was performed by a large team, which included the local fire department and other services.The man was taken to hospital for treatment and officials will conduct an investigation to find out what led to the fall. A construction worker is rescued after a fall in Fourways. (Supplied)24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.